    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\nYou're building an app that automatically sends personalized text messages. But something's not working! The app crashes when it tries to run the code.\r\n\r\n1. Look at the fnction `send_text(name)`. This function is supposed to print a message to someone by name.\r\n\r\n2. Try running the code. Notice the error that appears.\r\n\r\n3. Figure out what's wrong with the function call and fix it so the message sends correctly.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-laptop\"></i> **Coding Tip**\r\n\r\nIf your function uses a parameter in the definition, check that you're giving it everything it needs when you call it.",
